    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAdded right-click to open files using NVM in the registry. After opening the file, the first line of the file will add+q4D73. If open NVIM first and then edit the file, it will not appear. I didn't find this issue on Win11.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Add to the registry, right-click to open with nvim\n2. select a file\n3. right click open file\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nopen file, and no +q4D73 at first line.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nwindows 10\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwindows terminal 1.24.10921.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nother (windows install package)",
