        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> > Added right-click to open files using NVM in the registry\n> \n> I assume NVM means Nvim. What exactly is the registry entry? How you invoke Nvim, and what Windows passes to Nvim, are very relevant here...\n> \n> > I didn't find this issue on Win11.\n> \n> 👀\n\nYes, there is no such issue on Win11.\nAdded right-click to open files using NVM in the registry like this:\n\nWindows Registry Editor Version 5.00\n\n[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\\*\\shell\\Neovim]\n@=\"Open with Neovim\"\n\"Icon\"=\"C:\\\\Program Files\\\\Neovim\\\\bin\\\\nvim.exe\"\n\n[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\\*\\shell\\Neovim\\command]\n@=\"\\\"C:\\\\Program Files\\\\Neovim\\\\bin\\\\nvim.exe\\\" \\\"%1\\\"\"\n\n<img width=\"567\" height=\"188\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0219edc1-eeec-464a-8db5-2bc356ccdd07\" />",
